-- #371: the poly-`Num` int `/` arm ($mdk_value_div, wasm_preamble.mdk) must produce
-- the SAME coded [E-DIV-ZERO] stderr line native does, not a raw engine trap
-- ("divide by zero"). `divP`'s params are a generic `Num a` (isPolyNumBinop routes
-- them through the runtime value-tag-dispatched helper, wasm_emit.mdk), so this
-- exercises the poly path, not the concrete-Int static fallback (see
-- polynum_divmod_int.mdk for that control). Since #531, diff_wasm_modules.sh
-- compares stderr and exit code (not just stdout) for EVERY fixture generically,
-- so this no longer needs a bespoke per-fixture assert to tell a coded trap from a
-- bare engine trap — the stdout-only compare every other fixture used to get
-- ("before" == "before") could not, which is exactly why one existed here before.
divP a b = a / b

main =
  println "before"
  println (divP 1 0)
